{"title":"In the Drops: Silca’s new super sealant, a big bag from Thule, feathery Alpitude cages and Pro’s speedy gravel finishing kit","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/silca-ultimate-sealant","date":1743180885000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/silca-ultimate-sealant\">In the Drops: Silca’s new super sealant, a big bag from Thule, feathery Alpitude cages and Pro’s speedy gravel finishing kit</a></p>\n\n<p>The spring races are in full swing (or are they? I’m all disorientated now that there’s no non-paywalled TV coverage, thanks for that TNT), so this week our one-stop-shop race guides were out in full force, with ones published for Brugge-De Panne, <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/e3-saxo-bank-classic-2024-preview\">E3 Saxo Bank Classic</a> and <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/gent-wevelgem-preview\">Gent-Wevelgem</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The steady trickle of new kit launches that come at this time of year continued as well, with some new <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/new-continental-terra-adventure-tyre-blurs-the-line-between-gravel-and-mtb\">gravel tyres from Continental</a>, <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/maap-aeon-kit\">posh endurance garms from MAAP</a>, <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/ridley-ignite-gtx\">a mountain bike with drop bars from Ridley</a> and the official launch <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/van-rysel-rcr-f\">Van Rysel’s not-so-secret RCR-F</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Away from pro and tech, I got photographed looking sweaty and uncomfortable trying out <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/heat-training\">heat training</a>, which claims to offer similar fitness benefits to altitude camps in a much more practical package. Just be sure to bring a towel.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So that’s our content highlights rounded up. The only thing left to do? Learn more about some shiny new kit.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n<h2>Silca Ultimate sealant</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-2-970x647.webp\" alt=\"White bottle of Silca tyre sealant\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-2-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-2-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-2-768x512.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-2-1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-2-750x500.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-2-1140x760.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-2-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-2-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-2-350x233.webp 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-2.webp 2000w\" /><figcaption>Sam Challis</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Somewhat confusingly, the last Silca <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-tubeless-sealant\">tubeless sealant</a> was also ‘Ultimate’, but this new formula is apparently even ultimater. Silca is even willing to put its money where its mouth is to prove it: it has offered its sponsored riders $500 if they experience an unsealable flat during this year’s Life Time Grand Prix gravel series.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-1-970x647.webp\" alt=\"White bottle of Silca tyre sealant\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-1-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-1-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-1-768x512.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-1-1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-1-750x500.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-1-1140x760.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-1-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-1-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-1-350x233.webp 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-1.webp 2000w\" /><figcaption>Sam Challis</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The reason Silca is so confident is because it says it has <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/silca-ultimate-sealant-2025\">remedied the downsides of its original sealant</a>, namely a short lifespan and tricky install. A new blend of natural and synthetic latex creates a six month-plus lifespan, and the uniform use of shorter, single-strand carbon fibres means the sealant can be injected through tubeless valves without clogging, despite remaining able to seal 6mm+ holes.</p>\n\n\n\n<div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/subscriptions?utm_source=Web&amp;utm_medium=Banner&amp;utm_campaign=Banner+6\"><img width=\"970\" height=\"300\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-6-970x300.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-6-970x300.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-6-300x93.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-6-768x238.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-6-1536x476.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-6-2048x634.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-6-750x232.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-6-1140x353.webp 1140w\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Thule Chasm wheeled duffel bag</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-11-970x647.webp\" alt=\"Black Thule suitcase on grass\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-11-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-11-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-11-768x512.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-11-1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-11-750x500.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-11-1140x760.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-11-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-11-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-11-350x233.webp 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-11.webp 2000w\" /><figcaption>Sam Challis</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Trips away to create <em>Cyclist</em> magazine’s <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/big-ride\">Big Ride features</a> aren’t all fun and games (just mostly fun and games). There’s some pressure to ensure our riding gear arrives safely, and with fragile things such as <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-bike-helmet\">helmets</a> going up against the might of EasyJet baggage handlers we generally look for protection and robustness in our luggage to ensure our kit arrives unscathed. That way, our peerless content creation can unfold without disruption.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-14-970x647.webp\" alt=\"Open suitcase on grass\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-14-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-14-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-14-768x512.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-14-1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-14-750x500.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-14-1140x760.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-14-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-14-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-14-350x233.webp 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-14.webp 2000w\" /><figcaption>Sam Challis</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Swedish luggage brand Thule’s bag looks to fit the bill, that being the case. Its 130 litre capacity should swallow all the kit needed for even the longest riding trip with room to spare, and its natty compartments in the underside of the main flap and the top of the bag should help separate things out so a various riding bits and bobs can stay organised.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-13-970x647.webp\" alt=\"Black Thule suitcase on grass\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-13-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-13-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-13-768x512.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-13-1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-13-750x500.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-13-1140x760.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-13-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-13-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-13-350x233.webp 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-13.webp 2000w\" /><figcaption>Sam Challis</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Best of all, Thule is known for its excellent build quality. The polycarbonate lower shell and sturdy wheels look like they’ll stand up to the rigours of travel for years, and the main body fabric is water repellent, rip and tear resistant, and made from recycled materials as well. Pricing is at the premium end of the scale, but I can’t imagine this’ll be something you’ll need to think about replacing for a while.</p>\n\n\n\n<div>\n</div>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cyclist-track-days-2025-bikes-cannondale-supersix-evo\">Cyclist Track Days 2025 bikes #23: Cannondale SuperSix Evo</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/van-rysel-rcr-f\">Van Rysel launches RCR-F thoroughbred aero road bike</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/our-perfect-british-grand-depart\">We mapped out the 2027 British Tour de France Grand Départs</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/gent-wevelgem-preview\">Gent-Wevelgem 2025 preview: Route, favourites, how to watch and start list</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>Alpitude Superleggero cages</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-8-970x647.webp\" alt=\"Alpitude carbon bottle cage\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-8-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-8-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-8-768x512.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-8-1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-8-750x500.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-8-1140x760.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-8-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-8-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-8-350x233.webp 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-8.webp 2000w\" /><figcaption>Sam Challis</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Alpitude’s Superleggero cage lives up to its name, being able to lay claim to the title of lightest bottle cage on the market, beating Topeak’s Fezā R10S cage into second place by a whopping 0.5g.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Strips of Toray’s T800 carbon fibre are laid up and moulded in monocoque fashion (ie, as one piece) to achieve the weight. Higher grades of carbon could be used, but the risk of the thread-like structure becoming too brittle to flex and grip a bottle becomes too large.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As it is, Alpitude says the Superleggero is as user-friendly as any normal cage, but at 9.5g, is around a third of the weight.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>To find out more about the Alpitude Superleggero cage, visit <a href=\"https://alpitude.cc/product/superleggero-minimal-carbon-cage/\" target=\"_blank\">alpitude.cc</a></strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Pro Discover Aero bars and 10 stem</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-4-970x647.webp\" alt=\"Black pro bicycle handlebars\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-4-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-4-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-4-768x512.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-4-1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-4-750x500.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-4-1140x760.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-4-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-4-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-4-350x233.webp 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-4.webp 2000w\" /><figcaption>Sam Challis</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As the speeds in gravel racing continue to increase, aerodynamic equipment is becoming more relevant than ever for those that like to go fast on gravel, with the perk that its performance attributes translate pretty neatly onto the road as well. The latest bars and stem from Shimano’s components brand Pro serve as one of the best examples to date of that logic being applied to finishing kit.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>‘Aerodynamic gains in gravel frames and wheels for all-day riding and fast-paced racing have become the norm, yet dedicated cockpits have been in short supply,’ says Pro’s Niek Verbakel. ‘As such, we wanted to change that.’</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The tops of the Pro Discover Aero bars use an aerofoil cross section, but ultimately that’s chump change when it comes to improving aerodynamics. The real gains come in manipulating rider position to create an aggressive but sustainable position.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>‘The tops adopt a slight downslope and forward sweep to encourage the rider to get low without stressing the wrists,’ says Verbakel. ‘The slightly flared drops are compact, so easy to rest in for extended periods as well.’</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In an attempt to both enhance comfort and improve durability, Pro says it has added Dyneema – a strong yet flexible synthetic fibre – into the carbon composite as well, to absorb vibration and resist impacts.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-5-970x647.webp\" alt=\"Black pro bicycle handlebars\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-5-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-5-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-5-768x512.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-5-1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-5-750x500.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-5-1140x760.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-5-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-5-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-5-350x233.webp 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/in-the-drops-28-03-25-5.webp 2000w\" /><figcaption>Sam Challis</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Discover 10 stem is a simpler affair, using the same proven 7075 aluminium as other Pro stems, but it differs from those – and supports the bars’ aero pretensions – by using a more aggressive 10° angle to further help lower the rider’s body position.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Pro Discover Aero bars</h3>\n\n\n\n<div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<h3>Pro Discover 10 stem</h3>\n\n\n\n<div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div><div>\n<p><em><strong>Ad feature</strong></em></p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Enjoy the very best of Mallorca with Medfeel</h2>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"1200\" height=\"901\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/medfeel_01.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/medfeel_01.webp 1200w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/medfeel_01-300x225.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/medfeel_01-970x728.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/medfeel_01-768x577.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/medfeel_01-750x563.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/medfeel_01-1140x856.webp 1140w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>After weeks of lingering bad weather across Europe, the sun is finally making an appearance to welcome in the spring. What better time to start planning how to enjoy the sunshine?</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Medfeel</strong> is an elite local cycling company in Mallorca, and its focus is quite simply to ensure you get the <strong>best premium cycling experience</strong> for the best price quoted.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"http://t1.emails.cyclist.co.uk/r/?id=h707b77b9,bf7d981,bf7f314\" target=\"_blank\">Medfeel</a>’s clients are accommodated at the island’s most distinguished 4-star and 5-star boutique hotels, with every detail taken care of to ensure an exceptional stay.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"728\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/medfeel_02-970x728.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/medfeel_02-970x728.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/medfeel_02-300x225.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/medfeel_02-768x577.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/medfeel_02-750x563.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/medfeel_02-1140x856.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/medfeel_02.webp 1200w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Each trip is tailored to your specific needs</strong>, so that you can enjoy each memorable ride without having anything else to worry about. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s about getting an insider’s perspective on the very best of Mallorca, from the breathtaking scenic routes to the cultural traditions and the local gastronomy.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"728\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/medfeel_03-970x728.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/medfeel_03-970x728.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/medfeel_03-300x225.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/medfeel_03-768x577.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/medfeel_03-750x563.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/medfeel_03-1140x856.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/medfeel_03.webp 1200w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So why not immerse yourself in the local culture and find those hidden gems only local knowledge can unlock? </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Don’t be afraid to venture off the beaten path. Round up your cycling group and book an unforgettable cycling experience with Medfeel while there is space still available! </p>\n\n\n\n<div>\n<div><a href=\"https://www.medfeel.pro/?utm_source=magazine&amp;utm_medium=cyclist&amp;utm_campaign=newsletter_magazine_mar_28_2025&amp;deliveryName=FCP_2_DM321583\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Find out more</strong></a></div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div></div>\n\n\n\n<p><em><strong>Ad feature ends</strong></em></p>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<h2>What we’re into this week: Riding fixed around Australia</h2>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/1742376778357.gif\" alt=\"\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>Cycling across Australia isn’t for the faint of heart. Cycling LEJOG (or JOGLE) is hard enough, but since you can fit about 30 Englands inside Australia, crossing the Land Down Under is a totally different biscuit.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But that’s exactly what friend of the magazine Loz Walters is doing right now. First of all he’s riding the 5,500km Indian Pacific Wheel Ride from Perth on the west coast to Sydney on the east coast, and then he’s going to pony up and ride another 9,000km up and over northern Australia, back to Perth, the long way. At least it will be hard to get lost.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Oh, and he’s doing it on a fixie. <a href=\"https://ipwr25.maprogress.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Track his progress here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>There’s a record on the line, but most importantly, he’s riding in support of Mike Hall, the late godfather of ultracycling, by <a href=\"https://www.justgiving.com/page/lozwalters\" target=\"_blank\">raising money for the RNLI</a>. If you’re in a position to, all help is very welcome. And you can <a href=\"https://buymeacoffee.com/lozwalters\" target=\"_blank\">buy the poor lad a coffee here too</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Follow Loz’s or Ridefixedordietryin’s socials <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/ridefixedordietryin/\" target=\"_blank\">here</a></strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/newsletters\"><img width=\"970\" height=\"351\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-2-970x351.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-2-970x351.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-2-300x109.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-2-768x278.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-2-1536x556.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-2-2048x741.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-2-750x271.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-2-1140x412.jpg 1140w\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/silca-ultimate-sealant\">In the Drops: Silca’s new super sealant, a big bag from Thule, feathery Alpitude cages and Pro’s speedy gravel finishing kit</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Sam Challis &#124; Tech Editor","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"8120700bf044acb630d0098b5b40be7482de23046e5d07c020522dc39f3e9455","category":"Cycling"}